    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT356-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">makaṭ pōkkiya cevilittāy uraittatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by the foster-mother, who had let the daughter go. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT356">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> niḻalāṉ ṟavinta nīri lāriṭaik</l>
          <l> kaḻalōṉ kāppak kaṭukupu pōki</l>
          <l> yaṟucuṉai maruṅkiṉ maṟukupu venta</l>
          <l> vevvaṅ kaluḻi tavveṉak kuṭitti</l>
          <l> yāṅkuval lunaḷko ṟāṉē yēntiya</l>
          <l> cempoṟ puṉaikalat tamporik kalanta</l>
          <l> pālum palaveṉa vuṇṇāḷ</l>
          <l> kōlamai kuṟuntoṭit taḷiraṉ ṉōḷē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent2">In a difficult place without water, devoid of shade,</l>
          <l rend="indent">going hastily under the protection of the man with anklets,</l>
          <l rend="indent">[and] drinking troublesome muddy water that is hot, </l>
          <l rend="indent2">evaporated in swirls from subsiding mountain pools</l>
          <l>– how is she capable [of that], she,</l>
          <l>[tender] as a sprout, with [well-]fitting tight bracelets in a row,</l>
          <l>who, saying “[too] much”, does not eat even milk</l>
          <l rend="indent2">mixed with nice rice from a pot decorated with red gold,</l>
          <l rend="indent8">which she received ?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
